[normal]Written evidence from [bold]the Nursing and Midwifery Council[bold] (NMC [bold]00[bold]0[bold]1[bold])[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Introduction[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Responding to Francis[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]5.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To evaluate our education standards and review our code to ensure that Francis themes such as candour and compassion are appropriately covered.
[normal]5.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To raise our profile as recommended by the Francis report so that patients, the public and employers understand our role and get the support they need if they have concerns about a nurse or midwife.
[normal]5.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To implement the changes to our fitness to practise legislation announced by the Prime Minister in response to the Francis report and thereby deliver improvements to the timeliness and quality of our casework.
[normal]5.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To strengthen our collaborative work with other regulators – we have revised our memorandum of understanding with the CQC and will have new protocols for information sharing and joint work by the end of 2013. We want to extend this work to other UK regulators in 2014.
